From the a literal on the command line

$ kubectl create secret generic mysql-pass --from-literal=user=YOUR_USER
$ kubectl create secret generic mysql-pass --from-literal=password=YOUR_PASS

From a file: creates a generic secret named mysql-user from the 'mysql-username' file and mysql-pass from 'mysql-password' file.

$ kubectl create secret generic mysql-pass --from-file=./mysql-password